In many cases, dissolved CO2 is inferred to be the primary carbon source for abiotic organic synthesis in geologic systems.

We will follow the geologic convention here, and use the term Fischer-Tropsch-type (FTT) synthesis to refer in general to any surface-catalyzed reduction of an inorganic carbon source to organic matter.

